== About me
I am a Phd candidate in ([http://appliedmath.ucdavis.edu/ GGAM]) at UC Davis. I am lucky working with [https://www.math.ucdavis.edu/~sqma/ Shiqian Ma] and [https://sites.google.com/view/kriznakumar/home Krishnakumar Balasubramanian].


== Research
My research interests include
- Reinforcement learning and policy optimization for large language models
- Stochastic optimization, especially zeroth order optimization with variance reduction
- Zeroth order min-max optimization in deterministic and stochastic settings

== Publications

=== Large Language Models and Reinforcement Learning
. SFT Doesn't Always Hurt General Capabilities: Revisiting Domain-Specific Fine-Tuning in LLMs (with Jiacheng Lin, Kun Qian, et al.), ICLR 2025.
. ST-PPO: Stabilized Off-Policy Proximal Policy Optimization for Multi-Turn Agents Training (with Chenghao Li, Ahmed Elmahdy, Alex Boyd, et al.), COLM 2026.
. Reinforcement Learning in Inference Time: A Perspective from Successive Policy Iterations (with Xiangyu Zhang, Chenghao Li, et al.), NeurIPS 2025 Workshop on Reasoning and Planning for Large Language Models.
. GT2Vec: Large Language Models for Knowledge Graph Augmented Text Embedding (with Jiacheng Lin, Kun Qian, et al.), KDD 2024 Workshop on Structured Knowledge for Large Language Models.

=== Optimization
. Zeroth-Order Algorithms for Nonconvex-Strongly-Concave Minimax Problems with Improved Complexities (with Krishnakumar Balasubramanian, Shiqian Ma, Meisam Razaviyayn), Journal of Global Optimization, 87(2):709-740, 2023. An earlier version appeared at the NeurIPS 2020 Workshop.
. A Manifold Proximal Linear Method for Sparse Spectral Clustering with Application to Single-Cell RNA Sequencing Data Analysis (with Binyuan Liu, Shixiang Chen, Shiqian Ma, Lingzhou Xue, Hongyu Zhao), INFORMS Journal on Optimization, 2021.
. New Algorithms for Riemannian Optimization and Minimax Problems with Machine Learning, PhD Dissertation, University of California, Davis, 2022.
